        "contentData": [
          {
            "contentTypeKey": "48cee39d-6ba9-4599-b547-147a9bb31a82",
            "udi": "umb://element/0b91f17ce061499786ee3922db7a1cdf",
            "textbox": "<div class=\"OutlineElement Ltr SCXW196672360 BCX0\">\n<p class=\"Paragraph SCXW196672360 BCX0\"><strong><span class=\"NormalTextRun SCXW196672360 BCX0\">What can a doughnut teach us about economics?</span> </strong></p>\n</div>\n<div class=\"OutlineElement Ltr SCXW196672360 BCX0\">\n<p class=\"Paragraph SCXW196672360 BCX0\"><span class=\"NormalTextRun SCXW196672360 BCX0\">Traditionally, we’ve used cold hard GDP growth to determine economic success, but have we really thought this through? Since 1970, </span><a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://ourworldindata.org/grapher/global-gdp-over-the-long-run?time=earliest..2021\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"Hyperlink SCXW196672360 BCX0\"><span class=\"NormalTextRun SCXW196672360 BCX0\" data-ccp-charstyle=\"Hyperlink\">global GDP has increased more than fivefold</span></a><span class=\"NormalTextRun SCXW196672360 BCX0\">, but have we gotten any closer to making it off the treadmill? Simultaneously, </span><a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://ourworldindata.org/greenhouse-gas-emissions\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"Hyperlink SCXW196672360 BCX0\"><span class=\"NormalTextRun SCXW196672360 BCX0\" data-ccp-charstyle=\"Hyperlink\">global greenhouse gas emissions have almost doubled</span></a><span class=\"NormalTextRun SCXW196672360 BCX0\">, and billions of us still live without our basic needs being met.</span> </p>\n</div>\n<div class=\"OutlineElement Ltr SCXW196672360 BCX0\">\n<p class=\"Paragraph SCXW196672360 BCX0\"><span class=\"NormalTextRun SCXW196672360 BCX0\">That’s not really the return on investment we were hoping for.</span> </p>\n</div>\n<div class=\"OutlineElement Ltr SCXW196672360 BCX0\">\n<p class=\"Paragraph SCXW196672360 BCX0\"><strong><span class=\"NormalTextRun SCXW196672360 BCX0\">Introducing the doughnut</span> </strong></p>\n</div>\n<div class=\"OutlineElement Ltr SCXW196672360 BCX0\">\n<p class=\"Paragraph SCXW196672360 BCX0\"><span class=\"NormalTextRun SCXW196672360 BCX0\">The brainchild of economist Kate Raworth, the doughnut is a new model for measuring health of an economy and establishes new goalposts for policymaking.</span> </p>\n</div>\n<div class=\"OutlineElement Ltr SCXW196672360 BCX0\">\n<p class=\"Paragraph SCXW196672360 BCX0\"><span class=\"NormalTextRun SCXW196672360 BCX0\">The parameters are simple. We should ensure everyone’s basic needs, including everything from food, to housing, to political voice, are met. This lower threshold is called the social foundation and is derived from the </span><a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://sdgs.un.org/goals\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"Hyperlink SCXW196672360 BCX0\"><span class=\"NormalTextRun SCXW196672360 BCX0\" data-ccp-charstyle=\"Hyperlink\">sustainable development goals</span></a><span class=\"NormalTextRun SCXW196672360 BCX0\"> agreed by the United Nations.</span> </p>\n<p class=\"Paragraph SCXW196672360 BCX0\"> </p>\n<figure><img src=\"?rmode=max&amp;width=500&amp;height=500\" alt=\"This diagram shows an upper and lower boundary that explain what humanity's goals should be. It expresses that we need to meet people's basic material, social, and economic needs without further damaging the planet.\" width=\"500\" height=\"500\" data-udi=\"umb://media/3717c59e6b534fe79900581c1366bf93\" data-caption=\"Title: The Doughnut of social and planetary boundaries. Credit: Kate Raworth and Christian Guthier. CC-BY-SA 4.0 Citation: Raworth, K. (2017), Doughnut Economics: seven ways to think like a 21st century economist. London: Penguin Random House.\">\n<figcaption>Title: The doughnut of social and planetary boundaries. Credit: Kate Raworth and Christian Guthier. CC-BY-SA 4.0 Citation: Raworth, K. (2017), Doughnut Economics: seven ways to think like a 21st century economist. London: Penguin Random House.</figcaption>\n</figure>\n<figure><img src=\"?rmode=max&amp;width=500\" alt=\"This diagram shows how far we currently are from reaching the goals expressed as 'the safe and just space for humanity'. It expresses that there is currently too much climate change, biodiversity loss, land conversion and nitrogen and phosphorus loading, and that most people's basic needs are still not adequately being met.\" width=\"500\" height=\"419\" data-udi=\"umb://media/1a548171bf0d41f28b52703ddea689a5\" data-caption=\"Title: The Doughnut of social and planetary boundaries. Credit: Kate Raworth and Christian Guthier. CC-BY-SA 4.0 Citation: Raworth, K. (2017), Doughnut Economics: seven ways to think like a 21st century economist. London: Penguin Random House.\">\n<figcaption>Title: The Doughnut of social and planetary boundaries. Credit: Kate Raworth and Christian Guthier. CC-BY-SA 4.0 Citation: Raworth, K. (2017), Doughnut Economics: seven ways to think like a 21st century economist. London: Penguin Random House.</figcaption>\n</figure>\n<div class=\"OutlineElement Ltr SCXW244633895 BCX0\">\n<p class=\"Paragraph SCXW244633895 BCX0\"><span class=\"NormalTextRun SCXW244633895 BCX0\">However, we can only push our planet so far. Our activity takes place within the delicate confines of the natural world, and there’s only so much it can tolerate. Climate change, air pollution, and biodiversity loss all place our only home in jeopardy. This is where the upper limit comes in: the ecological ceiling (you’ll be unsurprised to hear that Sir David Attenborough is among the theory’s fans).</span> </p>\n</div>\n<div class=\"OutlineElement Ltr SCXW244633895 BCX0\">\n<p class=\"Paragraph SCXW244633895 BCX0\"><span class=\"NormalTextRun SCXW244633895 BCX0\"></span><span class=\"NormalTextRun CommentStart SCXW244633895 BCX0\">The area between these two goalposts is referred to as the safe and just space for humanity. Doughnut economics provides a roadmap for us to get there and stay there. </span> </p>\n</div>\n<div class=\"OutlineElement Ltr SCXW244633895 BCX0\">\n<p class=\"Paragraph SCXW244633895 BCX0\"><span class=\"NormalTextRun SCXW244633895 BCX0\">It favours thriving within our ecological constraints over endless GDP growth, distribution by design over speculation that wealth will trickle down, and viewing the economy for what it is – a complex system, embedded within the social and natural world.</span> </p>\n</div>\n<div class=\"OutlineElement Ltr SCXW244633895 BCX0\">\n<p class=\"Paragraph SCXW244633895 BCX0\"><strong><span class=\"NormalTextRun SCXW244633895 BCX0\">So, how can this work in practice?</span> </strong></p>\n</div>\n<div class=\"OutlineElement Ltr SCXW244633895 BCX0\">\n<p class=\"Paragraph SCXW244633895 BCX0\"><span class=\"NormalTextRun SCXW244633895 BCX0\">Just like there’s no one way to enjoy a doughnut, doughnut economics leaves plenty of room for pragmatism and codesign. It’s been adopted as a framework for measuring impact by businesses, cities, regions, and even a national park. </span> </p>\n</div>\n<div class=\"OutlineElement Ltr SCXW244633895 BCX0\">\n<p class=\"Paragraph SCXW244633895 BCX0\"><span class=\"NormalTextRun SCXW244633895 BCX0\">The West Midlands Combined Authority is one of these pioneers, and you can read more about how we’ve integrated doughnut economics into our </span><a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://www.wmca.org.uk/what-we-do/inclusive-growth/blog/#/article/what-is-inclusive-growth/\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"Hyperlink SCXW244633895 BCX0\"><span class=\"NormalTextRun SCXW244633895 BCX0\" data-ccp-charstyle=\"Hyperlink\">inclusive growth fundamentals here</span></a><span class=\"NormalTextRun SCXW244633895 BCX0\">. But what can we learn from our peers?</span> </p>\n</div>\n<div class=\"OutlineElement Ltr SCXW244633895 BCX0\">\n<p class=\"Paragraph SCXW244633895 BCX0\"><strong><span class=\"NormalTextRun SCXW244633895 BCX0\">Circular Amsterdam</span> </strong></p>\n</div>\n<div class=\"OutlineElement Ltr SCXW244633895 BCX0\">\n<p class=\"Paragraph SCXW244633895 BCX0\"><span class=\"NormalTextRun SCXW244633895 BCX0\">Amsterdam was the first place in the world to develop a </span><a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://www.kateraworth.com/wp/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/20200406-AMS-portrait-EN-Single-page-web-420x210mm.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"Hyperlink SCXW244633895 BCX0\"><span class=\"NormalTextRun SCXW244633895 BCX0\" data-ccp-charstyle=\"Hyperlink\">‘City Portrait’</span></a><span class=\"NormalTextRun SCXW244633895 BCX0\">, an application of doughnut economics’ methodology on a city-wide scale. The portrait questions what it would mean for Amsterdam’s people and natural environment to thrive, and for the city to respect the health of the planet and wellbeing of its inhabitants. Through this process, it identified several specific targets for policymaking spanning multiple sectors.</span> </p>\n</div>\n<div class=\"OutlineElement Ltr SCXW244633895 BCX0\">\n<p class=\"Paragraph SCXW244633895 BCX0\"><span class=\"NormalTextRun SCXW244633895 BCX0\">Furthermore, Amsterdam stands out for its local-level initiatives. For instance, in 2019, it pioneered the concept of ‘Doughnut Deals’ in the Bijlmer area, itself a story of neighbourhood renewal and newfound pride of place. This shone a welcome spotlight on community-led projects as a means of arriving at the doughnut from the bottom up.</span> </p>\n</div>\n<div class=\"OutlineElement Ltr SCXW244633895 BCX0\">\n<p class=\"Paragraph SCXW244633895 BCX0\"><span class=\"NormalTextRun SCXW244633895 BCX0\">In 2022, the city undertook its first </span><a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://doughnuteconomics.org/stories/amsterdam-donut-deal-day\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"Hyperlink SCXW244633895 BCX0\"><span class=\"NormalTextRun SCXW244633895 BCX0\" data-ccp-charstyle=\"Hyperlink\">‘Doughnut Deal Day’</span></a><span class=\"NormalTextRun SCXW244633895 BCX0\">, connecting hundreds of stakeholders from across the city to hash out solutions that covered everything from education to waste disposal. With the launch of the </span><a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"http://c//Users/willhiggins/Downloads/implementation-agenda-circular%20(1).pdf\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"Hyperlink SCXW244633895 BCX0\"><span class=\"NormalTextRun SCXW244633895 BCX0\" data-ccp-charstyle=\"Hyperlink\">Implementation Agenda for a Circular Amsterdam</span></a><span class=\"NormalTextRun SCXW244633895 BCX0\">, this approach has gone all the way up to the mayor’s office. Something is clearly working.</span> </p>\n</div>\n<div class=\"OutlineElement Ltr SCXW244633895 BCX0\">\n<p class=\"Paragraph SCXW244633895 BCX0\"><strong><span class=\"NormalTextRun SCXW244633895 BCX0\">A Regenerative Melbourne</span> </strong></p>\n</div>\n<div class=\"OutlineElement Ltr SCXW244633895 BCX0\">\n<p class=\"Paragraph SCXW244633895 BCX0\"><span class=\"NormalTextRun SCXW244633895 BCX0\">Taking the doughnut down under, Greater Melbourne was the first city region in Australia to produce a city portrait – </span><a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://static1.squarespace.com/static/64251f00583fb50462a22eeb/t/6448c0ee2f1dae40001f13a7/1682489626087/Towards_a_Regenerative_Melbourne_Report_April_2021.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"Hyperlink SCXW244633895 BCX0\"><span class=\"NormalTextRun SCXW244633895 BCX0\" data-ccp-charstyle=\"Hyperlink\">the Melbourne Doughnut</span></a><span class=\"NormalTextRun SCXW244633895 BCX0\">. It’s an impressive document, mapping the region’s existing strategic plans onto the doughnut and incorporating the results of workshops undertaken with the community. </span> </p>\n</div>\n<div class=\"OutlineElement Ltr SCXW244633895 BCX0\">\n<p class=\"Paragraph SCXW244633895 BCX0\"><span class=\"NormalTextRun SCXW244633895 BCX0\">The strategy is the result of sustained collaboration with stakeholders. Dozens of academics, six universities, and over 150 experts contributed to the project. This has generated ideas, insight, and intelligence that wouldn’t have otherwise been available to policymakers in the city region. </span> </p>\n</div>\n<div class=\"OutlineElement Ltr SCXW244633895 BCX0\">\n<p class=\"Paragraph SCXW244633895 BCX0\"><span class=\"NormalTextRun SCXW244633895 BCX0\">In both cases, the doughnut has provided these areas with a map for navigating the defining issues of the 21</span><span class=\"NormalTextRun Superscript SCXW244633895 BCX0\" data-fontsize=\"11\">st</span><span class=\"NormalTextRun SCXW244633895 BCX0\"> Century. The pioneers of doughnut economics have found a way to make growth work for their places, rather than treating it as an end in itself. It’s only natural to question the rules of the game in light of new information.</span> </p>\n</div>\n<div class=\"OutlineElement Ltr SCXW244633895 BCX0\">\n<p class=\"Paragraph SCXW244633895 BCX0\"><span class=\"NormalTextRun SCXW244633895 BCX0\">The lesson from these examples is that by meaningfully engaging with local communities and absorbing the expertise of regional stakeholders, we can pin down what the safe and just space for humanity looks like city by city, and region by region.</span> </p>\n</div>\n<div class=\"OutlineElement Ltr SCXW244633895 BCX0\">\n<p class=\"Paragraph SCXW244633895 BCX0\"><span class=\"NormalTextRun CommentStart SCXW244633895 BCX0\">A well-made doughnut really does make everything a bit better.</span> </p>\n</div>\n<div class=\"OutlineElement Ltr SCXW244633895 BCX0\">\n<p class=\"Paragraph SCXW244633895 BCX0\"><span class=\"NormalTextRun SCXW244633895 BCX0\">If you want to read more about why GDP may be approaching its sell by date, why not check out ‘</span><a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://www.wmca.org.uk/what-we-do/inclusive-growth/blog/#/article/the-problem-with-economic-growth-why-our-current-economic-system-has-the-wrong-focus/\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"Hyperlink SCXW244633895 BCX0\"><span class=\"NormalTextRun SCXW244633895 BCX0\" data-ccp-charstyle=\"Hyperlink\">The problem with economic growth: why our current economic system has the wrong focus?’</span></a><span class=\"NormalTextRun SCXW244633895 BCX0\">.</span> </p>\n</div>\n<p> </p>\n<p class=\"Paragraph SCXW196672360 BCX0\"> </p>\n</div>"
          }
        ],
